article.headline: Jackson St. 83, MVSU 73
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. -- Jenirro Bush scored 25 points to lead Jackson State to an 83-73 win over Mississippi Valley State on Saturday night. Tyrone Hanson and Grant Maxey each added 17 points for the Tigers (11-9, 7-1 Southwestern Athletic Conference), who have won three in a row. Jackson State led 38-31 at halftime and finished 24 of 56 from the field (42.9 percent) and 31 of 42 from the free-throw line (73.8 percent) for the game. D'Angelo Jackson scored 22 points to lead the Delta Devils (7-14, 6-2), who had their five-game winning streak snapped. Kevin Burwell added 10 points. MVSU was outrebounded 46-31 and shot 21 of 53 from the floor (39.6 percent). The Delta Devils saw their best conference start since the 2005-06 season (6-1) come to an end as well. Bush increased his scoring average to 14.7 points per game, which is tied for the second-highest average in the SWAC.
